  "title": "Quality Assurance Personnel",
  "description": "<p>Traditional Chinese Medicine (TCM) manufacturing and Good Manufacturing Practice experience and knowledge is preferred as candidates are to check and ensure that starting materials, packaging materials and finished TCM products meet the standard requirements.</p><ol><li>Knowledge of Chinese Herbs is also preferred.</li><li>Candidates are required to draft documents related to the department, as well as GMP documents in Chinese.</li><li>Candidates are also required to supervise the production line and assess quality standards of TCM products during production and laboratory testing. </li><li>Candidates are required to learn about laboratory equipment such as HPLC, ICPOES, pH meter, as well as microbial testing techniques so as to supervise and verify that work is performed properly and correctly.</li><li>Candidates are required to be meticulous in recording and organising documentation, and be familiar with Microsoft Word and Microsoft Excel applications.</li></ol>",
